    <body>
        <p>Approved by the Localization Industry Standards Association (LISA) and the International Organization for Standardization (ISO), <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet1">Termbase eXchange (TBX) </MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet2">TBX </MadCap:conditionalText>is an open, XML-based international standard used for exchanging structured terminological data. One difference between a TBX file and a Translation Memory eXchange (TMX) file is that a TBX file handles multiple languages, whereas a TMX file handles only two languages.</p>
    </body>
</html>